    "Notes": [
      "1 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "2 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "6 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "7 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "8 : Booting from Cisco FlexFlash SD cards is supported, please check with the OS vendors for details. Also reference http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/servers-unified-computing/ucs-c-series-rack-servers/whitepaper-c11-734876.html",
      "9 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "11 : A Cisco OEM Customized ESX ISO maybe required for installation. Custom ISOs contain the minimum driver level for installation, please check the Cisco HCL for the supported driver versions. Custom ISOs are available from VMware.com > Downloads > VMware vSphere > Drivers and Tools > Custom ISOs",
      "12 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "15 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "16 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "20 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "21 : Drivers can be found on the latest 3.2(3) B-Series Driver ISO",
      "24 : Enable FCP error recovery in the service profile adapter policy",
      "26 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "28 : Direct attach virtual appliances connecting to external storage are not supported. Qualified direct attach virtual appliances with internal storage only are supported",
      "30 : Libraries are supported while using Automated Cartridge System Library Software (ACSLS) 8.3 and above or directly connected using Fibre Channel. The SL8500 requires ACSLS where the other libraries, ACSLS is optional.",
      "31 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "34 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "43 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "44 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC. ENIC will no longer be supported with 6.5 and later.",
      "47 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "53 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "54 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "55 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "56 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "57 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "58 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "59 : Direct connect of tape libraries is not supported",
      "61 : RHEL 7.4 is not supported on IBM SVC, XIV, Storwize and FlashSystems at this time",
      "62 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "63 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "69 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "114 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A250 is supported",
      "115 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A220 is supported",
      "116 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "117 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "118 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects"

      "1 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "2 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "6 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "7 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "8 : Booting from Cisco FlexFlash SD cards is supported, please check with the OS vendors for details. Also reference http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/servers-unified-computing/ucs-c-series-rack-servers/whitepaper-c11-734876.html",
      "9 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "11 : A Cisco OEM Customized ESX ISO maybe required for installation. Custom ISOs contain the minimum driver level for installation, please check the Cisco HCL for the supported driver versions. Custom ISOs are available from VMware.com > Downloads > VMware vSphere > Drivers and Tools > Custom ISOs",
      "12 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "14 : To use the GPU in Grid mode, download the drivers from https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/",
      "15 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "16 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "20 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "21 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.0(4) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "24 : Enable FCP error recovery in the service profile adapter policy",
      "26 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "30 : Libraries are supported while using Automated Cartridge System Library Software (ACSLS) 8.3 and above or directly connected using Fibre Channel. The SL8500 requires ACSLS where the other libraries, ACSLS is optional.",
      "31 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "34 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "38 : Requires the UCSB-LSTOR-PT PCI Passthrough Adapter. Not supported with the UCSB-MRAID12G or UCSB-MRAID12G-HE Adapter",
      "43 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "47 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "50 : Not supported on UCS the 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "53 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "54 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "55 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "56 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "57 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "58 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "59 : Direct connect of tape libraries is not supported",
      "62 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "63 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "67 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "94 : GPU drivers in pass-through mode are inbox",
      "111 : No support for VMWare 6.5u2 with MDS 9718 (32G) switch at this time",
      "113 : Supported Fibre channel SFP are 16G and 32G only.",
      "114 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC included in the Operating system",
      "117 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "118 : UEFI boot is not supported with 13XX VIC adapter",
      "119 : OS Path recovery fails after reboot of switch N5672UP connected to FI via FC unified port",
      "120 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "121 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "122 : Under unique conditions, intermittent frame drops could occur between Cisco UCS and MDS switches, please refer to CDETs CSCvr53596",
      "124 : Currently, only VMware ESXi 6.7 U2 is supported. This limitation will soon be removed",
      "125 : Hitachi arrays logout from the initiator when there are out of order frames or frame drops due to port channel member changes and other scenarios. This results in LUN paths going offline for few seconds.",
      "126 : Appliance Port is not supported at 25Gb, since no FEC support on NetApp E-Series arrays and option to disable FEC is not available on 6454/64108 FI's",
      "127 : NVMEoF supported in both FC - End Host Mode and FC - Switch Mode, refer storage / adaptor interoperability matrix for the supported OS's"

    "Notes": [
      "3 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "5 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "7 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC. ENIC will no longer be supported with 6.5 and later.",
      "11 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "13 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "18 : GPU drivers in pass-through mode are inbox",
      "19 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "20 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "21 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "23 : Libraries are supported while using Automated Cartridge System Library Software (ACSLS) 8.3 and above or directly connected using Fibre Channel. The SL8500 requires ACSLS where the other libraries, ACSLS is optional.",
      "25 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "26 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "29 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "30 : FC-NVME supported",
      "31 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "34 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "35 : Direct connect of tape libraries is not supported",
      "38 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "40 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "41 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "43 : To use the GPU in Grid mode, download the drivers from https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/",
      "44 : Enable FCP error recovery in the service profile adapter policy",
      "45 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "46 : Requires the UCSB-LSTOR-PT PCI Passthrough Adapter. Not supported with the UCSB-MRAID12G or UCSB-MRAID12G-HE Adapter",
      "48 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "51 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "54 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "55 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "58 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "60 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "61 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "63 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "66 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "67 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "70 : Booting from Cisco FlexFlash SD cards is supported, please check with the OS vendors for details. Also reference http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/servers-unified-computing/ucs-c-series-rack-servers/whitepaper-c11-734876.html",
      "71 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.0(4) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "72 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(1) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "75 : NVMEoF supported in both FC - End Host Mode and FC - Switch Mode, refer storage / adaptor interoperability matrix for the supported OS's",
      "77 : Windows Server 2019 with VIC14xx  is supported with the hotfix KB5001384 installed",
      "80 : This is the minimum driver version supported by Cisco. Any version above this driver is supported in the specific GRID branch. Refer https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/ for more details",
      "81 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A220 is supported",
      "82 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A400 is supported",
      "83 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A700 is supported",
      "84 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A800 is supported",
      "85 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A250 is supported",
      "88 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A900 is supported"

    "Notes": [
      "1 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "4 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "5 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "7 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC. ENIC will no longer be supported with 6.5 and later.",
      "9 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(1) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "10 : Requires the UCSB-LSTOR-PT PCI Passthrough Adapter. Not supported with the UCSB-MRAID12G or UCSB-MRAID12G-HE Adapter",
      "11 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "12 : FC-NVME supported",
      "13 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "24 : Booting from Cisco FlexFlash SD cards is supported, please check with the OS vendors for details. Also reference http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/servers-unified-computing/ucs-c-series-rack-servers/whitepaper-c11-734876.html",
      "25 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "26 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(2) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "29 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "37 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "38 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "39 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "41 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "43 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "44 : To use the GPU in Grid mode, download the drivers from https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/",
      "47 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "48 : NVMEoF supported in both FC - End Host Mode and FC - Switch Mode, refer storage / adaptor interoperability matrix for the supported OS's",
      "49 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "50 : Windows Server 2019 with VIC14xx  is supported with the hotfix KB5001384 installed",
      "54 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "55 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "56 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "57 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "59 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "60 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "63 : This is the minimum driver version supported by Cisco. Any version above this driver is supported in the specific GRID branch. Refer https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/ for more details",
      "64 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "65 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "66 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "67 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "68 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "69 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "73 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A250 is supported",
      "74 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A220 is supported",
      "75 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A400 is supported",
      "76 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A700 is supported",
      "77 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A800 is supported",
      "80 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A900 is supported"

    "Notes": [
      "1 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "2 : FC-NVME supported",
      "3 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "4 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "5 : This is the minimum driver version supported by Cisco. Any version above this driver is supported in the specific GRID branch. Refer https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/ for more details",
      "6 : Libraries are supported while using Automated Cartridge System Library Software (ACSLS) 8.3 and above or directly connected using Fibre Channel. The SL8500 requires ACSLS where the other libraries, ACSLS is optional.",
      "10 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "11 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "12 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "13 : Windows Server 2019 with VIC14xx  is supported with the hotfix KB5001384 installed",
      "14 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "15 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "16 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "18 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "19 : To use the GPU in Grid mode, download the drivers from https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/",
      "21 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "22 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "23 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "24 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC. ENIC will no longer be supported with 6.5 and later.",
      "27 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "28 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "30 : Enable FCP error recovery in the service profile adapter policy",
      "31 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "32 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "33 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "35 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "36 : NVMEoF supported in both FC - End Host Mode and FC - Switch Mode, refer storage / adaptor interoperability matrix for the supported OS's",
      "37 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "38 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(3) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "39 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "42 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "43 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "44 : Direct connect of tape libraries is not supported",
      "45 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "47 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "48 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(1) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "50 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "57 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A700 is supported",
      "58 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A800 is supported",
      "59 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A250 is supported",
      "60 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A220 is supported",
      "61 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A400 is supported",
      "63 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(2) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "68 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A900 is supported"

    "Notes": [
      "1 : Certain Cisco Fabric Interconnects of the 6200 series have an OUI which will prevent FC port channels from connecting. This issue is outlined in CSCty04686 and can be mitigated by having your upstream Nexus 5000 code at a minimum version 6.0(2)N1(2), or MDS as minimum version 5.2(6)N1(4).",
      "2 : NFNIC is the native version of the FNIC. FNIC will no longer be supported with 6.7 U1 and later.",
      "3 : Code levels greater than or equal to these listed versions are deemed by Cisco to be interoperable",
      "5 : NFS or CIFS data access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "6 : Minimum FW is 4.2.1. VmWare's HCL may not always be in sync with Cisco's HCL. Please refer to VmWare's KB 2030818",
      "7 : To use the GPU in Grid mode, download the drivers from https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/",
      "9 : FC-NVME supported",
      "10 : FCoE is not supported at this time",
      "12 : Specific switch features must be supported on all switches used, please consult release notes for each switch product to determine support for the desired feature",
      "14 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirements for storage arrays configured to use iSCSI (Data Only), NFS, or CIFS when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port",
      "15 : NENIC is the native version of the ENIC. ENIC will no longer be supported with 6.5 and later.",
      "16 : ESX NPIV Host Feature is not supported",
      "17 : NVMEoF supported in both FC - End Host Mode and FC - Switch Mode, refer storage / adaptor interoperability matrix for the supported OS's",
      "19 : Brocade Family FOS release trains, 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4, 8.0, 8.1 and 8.2 and their updates, unless otherwise stated are supported",
      "20 : Non-default adapter settings are typically required by storage vendors and found on their support list",
      "22 : Supported for NFS/CIFS access via appliance ports on the Fabric Interconnect",
      "24 : The Storage and Switch vendors interoperability matrix should be consulted for information regarding which software and hardware (arrays and switches) versions are supported",
      "25 : Cisco UCS has no interoperability requirement for switch configured to use Ethernet when connected through UCS Fabric Interconnect Uplink Port or Appliance Port",
      "26 : FC/FCoE direct attached storage arrays (Fabric Interconnects in FC Switching Mode) supported",
      "29 : This is the minimum driver version supported by Cisco. Any version above this driver is supported in the specific GRID branch. Refer https://docs.nvidia.com/grid/ for more details",
      "30 : Not supported on UCS 6200 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "31 : iSCSI Boot is supported. Both Appliance and Uplink ports are supported unless otherwise noted",
      "32 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.2(1) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "34 : Enable FCP error recovery in the service profile adapter policy",
      "36 : Multiple array and switch models supported with UCS by the storage vendor are on their support list",
      "37 : Direct connect of tape libraries is not supported",
      "38 : UCSM-configured iSCSI boot is supported",
      "40 : Not supported on UCS Mini",
      "41 : Windows Server 2019 with VIC14xx  is supported with the hotfix KB5001384 installed",
      "42 : UEFI boot is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) ",
      "45 : Libraries are supported while using Automated Cartridge System Library Software (ACSLS) 8.3 and above or directly connected using Fibre Channel. The SL8500 requires ACSLS where the other libraries, ACSLS is optional.",
      "46 : Drivers are included in the OS",
      "48 : For VMware VSAN deployment, please refer VSAN HCL for driver and firmware compatibility",
      "49 : iSCSI data LUN access if the storage array is directly connected to UCS Fabric Interconnects using Appliance Ports is supported",
      "50 : UCS Fabric Interconnect must be in FC End Host mode and upstream switch NPIV enabled",
      "51 : Appliance port is not supported with Chelsio iWARP Storage adapter (feature code AHB7) on UCS 6300 Series Fabric Interconnects",
      "55 : Drivers can be found on the latest 4.1(2) Driver ISOs or OS Based ISOs",
      "57 : Tested with Purity 6.1.5",
      "58 : NVMeoF is supported on ESXi 7.0U2, RHEL 8.3, SLES 15 SP2",
      "61 : Windows SAN boot in UEFI mode with Pure Storage fails. Please contact Pure Storage for resolution",
      "65 : ESXi 7.0u3 goes into PSOD when Service Profile Migration from one node to another is finished. Refer: CDCwc03108",
      "66 : PowerMax 2500 and 8500 are only supported in VxBlock",
      "67 : PowerStore T models are only supported in VxBlock",
      "69 : In 4.2(1i) build, when a user performs hard or soft reset of IOM 2208, the status of backplane ports goes down. Please refer to bug CSCwd44322.",
      "70 : NVMEoFC (Fabric Interconnects in FC End Host Mode) supported",
      "71 : Only End Host Mode is supported",
      "72 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A250 is supported",
      "73 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A220 is supported",
      "74 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A400 is supported",
      "75 : UEFI SAN boot is not supported with NetApp ASA (All San Array) variants.",
      "76 : All SAN Array variant NetApp ASA AFF A700 is supported",
      "77 : FC (Fabric Interconnects in FC End Host Mode) supported"
    ],
